l Street|year=1935|publisher=Grosset and Dunlap|ref=harv}} \n*{{cite book|last=Gordon|first=Meryl|year=2015|title=The Phantom of Fifth Avenue: The Mysterious Life and Scandalous Death of Heiress Huguette Clark|publisher=Grand Central Publishing|ref=harv|isbn=978-1-455-51265-2}}\n*{{cite book|last=MacGibbon|first=Elma|title=Leaves of Knowledge|publisher=Shaw & Borden Co.|year=1904|url=https://www.sos.wa.gov/legacy/publicationsviewer/?title=Leaves%20of%20knowledge&id=63&page=7|ref=harv}} \n*{{cite book|last=MacMillan|first=Donald|title=Smoke Wars: Anaconda Copper, Montana Air Pollution, and the Courts, 1890\u20131924|publisher= Montana Historical Society Press|year=2000|isbn= 978-0-917-29865-3|ref=harv}}\n*{{cite book|last1=Malone|first1=Michael P.|title=The Battle for Butte: Mining and Politics on the Northern Frontier, 1864\u20131906|publisher=[[University of Washington Press]]|year=2006|isbn= 978-0-295-80219-0|orig-year=1981|ref=harv}}\n*{{cite journal|last=Malone|first=Michael|year=1985|title=The Close of the Copper Century|journal=Montana: The Magazine of Western History|volume=35|pages=69\u201372}}\n*{{cite book|last1=Malone|first1=Michael|last2=Roeder|first2=Richard|last3=Lang|first3=William|year=1991|title=Montana: A History of Two Centuries|publisher=University of Washington Press|location=Seattle|ref=harv|isbn=978-0-295-97129-2}}\n*{{cite journal|last=McCarthy|first=Bob J.|title=Re-Claiming Butte: The Doctrine of Subjacent Support|issue=49|volume=267|journal=Montana Law Review|year=1988}}\n*{{cite book|last=Murphy|first=Mary|title=Mining Cultures: Men, Women, and Leisure in Butte, 1914\u201341|url=https://archive.org/details/miningculturesme0000murp|url-access=registration|publisher=University of Illinois Press|year=1997|isbn= 978-0-252-06569-9 |ref=harv}}\n*{{cite book|last=Nash|first=June|year=1993|orig-year=1979|title=We Eat the Mines and the Mines Eat Us|work=[[Columbia University Press]]|isbn=978-0-231-08051-4|ref=harv}}\n*{{cite book|last=Punke|first=Michael|year=2006|title=Fire and Brimstone: The North Butte Mining Disaster of 1917|publisher=Hachette Books|ref=harv|isbn=978-1-401-30889-6|url-access=registration|url=https://archive.org/details/firebrimstonenor00punk}}\n*{{cite book |editor-last1=Ring |editor-first1=Trudy |editor-last2=Watson |editor-first2=Noelle |editor-last3=Schellinger |editor-first3=Paul |year=2013 |title=The Americas: International Dictionary of Historic Places |publisher=Routledge |isbn=978-1-134-25930-4 |orig-year=1996 |ref=harv}}\n*{{cite book|last1=Shovers|first1= B.|last2= Fiege|first2= M| last3= Martin|first3=F.|last4=Quivik|first4= F|year=1991|title=Butte and Anaconda Revisited: An Overview of Early-Day Mining and Smelting in Montana|publisher=Butte Historical Society; Klepetko Chapter, Society for Industrial Archeology|ref=harv}}\n*{{cite book|last=Smith|first=Duane|year=2008|title=Rocky Mountain Heartland: Colorado, Montana, and Wyoming in the Twentieth Century|publisher=University of Arizona Press|ref=harv|isbn=978-0-816-52759-5}}\n*{{cite journal|last=Wyckoff|first=William|year=1995|title=Postindustrial Butte|journal=The Geographical Review|volume=85|number=4|pages=478\u201397|jstor=215921|doi=10.2307/215921}}\n{{refend}}\n\n==Further reading==\n===Pollution and toxic cleanup===\n'''Bibliographic materials'''\n{{refbegin|2}}\n* Barnett, Harold C. ''Toxic Debts and the Superfund Dilemma'' (University of North Carolina Press, 1994)\n* Barry, Bridget R. \"Toxic Tourism: Promoting the Berkeley Pit and Industrial Heritage in Butte, Montana.\" (2012). [http://digitalcommons.unl.edu/cgi/viewcontent.cgi?article=1050&context=historydiss online]\n* Bookspan, Shelley. \"Junk It, or Junket?\" ''Public Historian'' (2001) 23#2 pp.&nbsp;5\u20138 [https://www.jstor.org/stable/10.1525/tph.2001.23.2.5 in JSTOR]\n*Capek, Stella M. 1992. Environmental Justice, Regulation, and the Local Community.\" International Journal of Health Services 22(4):729\u2013746.\n*Chess, C. and Purcell, K. 1999. Public p